  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Shelter Repair and Transitional Shelter Assistance in Support of Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan is descending into the worst humanitarian crisis in the world. Amidst the backdrop of an already dire situation following 40 years of war, economic decline, price increases, and rising poverty, in 2021 the people of Afghanistan faced intensified conflict, the worst drought in 27 years, the withdrawal of international forces and then the takeover of the country by the Taliban in August. 24.4 million people &#x2013; 55 per cent of the population &#x2013; are in need of humanitarian assistance in 2022, a 30 per cent increase from last year. Under this project, IOM is distributing cash for transitional shelter and shelter repair to families in Badghis, Balkh, Parwan and Wardak provinces. These include in internally displaced persons (IDPs), natural disaster affected/displaced and other vulnerable groups.</narrative>
  </description>
